<item>
            <title>[SEC-50] Event not firing from DaoAuthenticationProvider</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-50</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&quot;DaoAuthenticationProvider.java around line 300, publishes an&lt;br/&gt;
AuthenticationSuccessEvent when the user has logged in.  However - it&lt;br/&gt;
only does this if the cache wasn&apos;t used... This seems odd and incorrect&lt;br/&gt;
to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since this sequence of events misses the second event :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1)       login as user A - event is fired&lt;br/&gt;
2)       logout&lt;br/&gt;
3)       login as user A - event isn&apos;t fired&lt;/p&gt;</description>
